title: Northwestern's Trevor Cunningham is lehighvalleylive Football Player of the Week
text:
Trevor Cunningham , Northwestern 
The junior wide receiver/defensive back had a night to remember as he helped the Tigers pull of a 24-21 win over Southern Lehigh. 
Cunningham had a hand in three turnovers, hauling in two interceptions and adding a fumble recovery. He also recorded six catches for 120 yards, becoming the first player in school history to have two games of 100-plus receiving yards in a season -- doing it in back-to-back games. 
On Northwestern's game-winning drive, Cunningham came up clutch when he caught a pass on fourth-and-10 and later made a grab off a deflected pass for a big gain.
